somewhere to stop.

00:36.504 --> 00:38.070
Don't worry about it.
It's like a big resort.

00:38.072 --> 00:39.371
There'll be signs for it
everywhere--

00:39.373 --> 00:40.739
Oh, I remember this well,
joel...
What?

00:40.741 --> 00:42.408
Your instinctive
sense of direction.

00:42.410 --> 00:43.542
We will get somewhere,

00:43.544 --> 00:44.777
But it won't be
the trauma conference.

00:44.779 --> 00:46.578
It'll be a b&b
where you make your own jam.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.614
Ouch! Holy!

00:48.616 --> 00:50.115
You know what?
(chuckles)

00:50.117 --> 00:51.550
One--my jam was delicious.

00:51.552 --> 00:53.185
Two--you had an excellent--
joel, that's not the point.

00:53.187 --> 00:55.788
You had an excellent time
on that trip.

00:55.790 --> 00:57.089
And you know what?
For the record,

00:57.091 --> 00:58.524
I cannot believe
that charlie--

00:58.526 --> 01:00.225
You know, I can't believe
that any man would give up

01:00.227 --> 01:02.227
A dirty weekend with you
at a medical conference

01:02.229 --> 01:03.595
Just to go and pick up
his friend at the airport,

01:03.597 --> 01:06.098
I'm just saying.
It's ford.
It's his best friend.

01:06.100 --> 01:07.299
(singsongy) dirty weekend.

01:07.301 --> 01:09.268
That's why you don't
have any friends.

01:09.270 --> 01:12.137
By the way, charlie is coming.
He's just running late.

01:12.139 --> 01:14.239
(chuckles) hey,
there's a gas station.

01:14.241 --> 01:15.307
Pull over.

01:15.309 --> 01:16.675
You got it.

01:16.677 --> 01:25.284
