(gasps)

02:37.491 --> 02:39.725
Oh.
Oh.

02:39.727 --> 02:42.361
(chuckles)

02:42.363 --> 02:43.662
(groans)

02:43.664 --> 02:45.797
Charles...

02:45.799 --> 02:47.466
You can fix this, right?

02:50.937 --> 02:53.405
Where are you going?

02:53.407 --> 02:55.874
I'm late,
and I don't really want

02:55.876 --> 02:57.709
To give my presentation
in a pair of jeans.

02:57.711 --> 03:00.312
Ooh, I remember this one.
What?

03:00.314 --> 03:01.880
The inevitable breakdown
that happens

03:01.882 --> 03:03.382
Whenever you think
you're gonna be late.

03:03.384 --> 03:04.883
Okay,
this isn't a breakdown.

03:04.885 --> 03:06.518
I have to give a speech
on the laparoscopic repair

03:06.520 --> 03:08.754
Of diaphragmatic injuries
in an hour and a half.

03:08.756 --> 03:10.355
And the last time I checked,
we were, oh,

03:10.357 --> 03:11.790
Two hours away
from the damn hotel.

03:11.792 --> 03:14.927
We're closer than two hours.

03:14.929 --> 03:17.863
No, no, no.
No, it's okay, love.

03:17.865 --> 03:20.933
I've got it.

03:30.643 --> 03:33.378
Okay. So, uh...

03:33.380 --> 03:35.681
Do you want me to change
the dinner reservation then?

03:35.683 --> 03:37.382
(charlie) uh, probably.

03:37.384 --> 03:39.251
I'm sorry, honey. I know this
was supposed to be our weekend--

03:39.253 --> 03:40.953
Give me that.
Give me that.

03:40.955 --> 03:42.988
Alex reid,
you gorgeous woman,

03:42.990 --> 03:45.390
Lover of charles,
healer of mankind.

03:45.392 --> 03:48.493
Shouldn't you be in some
war zone somewhere, ford--

03:48.495 --> 03:51.797
Sneaking into some
beautiful woman's tent?

03:51.799 --> 03:54.266
(chuckles)
alex, I love you.

03:54.268 --> 03:55.834
I know charles loves you.

03:55.836 --> 03:57.970
But you're gonna have to stay--
for the moment at least--

03:57.972 --> 04:00.405
Separated, for I am in need
of a physician.

04:00.407 --> 04:02.808
And the physician I need
is the same man that you love.

04:02.810 --> 04:04.610
Charles is his name.

04:04.612 --> 04:05.777
Are you stoned?

04:05.779 --> 04:07.679
No. No. It's probably
the pain meds.

04:07.681 --> 04:09.381
This is very real,
I assure you.

04:09.383 --> 04:11.550
There, she totally
forgives you.

04:11.552 --> 04:14.553
Up his dopamine, and give him
25 mikes of fentanyl.

04:14.555 --> 04:16.021
And hit him over the head
with a baseball bat.

04:16.023 --> 04:17.623
(chuckles)
hey, um,

04:17.625 --> 04:20.025
I will get on the road
as soon as I can. But, um...

04:20.027 --> 04:23.295
Ford's...
Kind of in a bad way.

04:23.297 --> 04:26.431
(sighs) in a bad way,
like, hungover?

04:26.433 --> 04:29.434
No. Bad like his leg
is mangled and he's septic.

04:29.436 --> 04:32.337
I'm sorry, honey.
I gotta go.
(sighs) he's your friend.

04:32.339 --> 04:34.573
Fix his leg.
(sighs) I love you.

04:34.575 --> 04:35.941
Love you.

04:35.943 --> 04:38.543
(cell phone beeps)

04:42.715 --> 04:45.651
(gas tank lid clunks)

04:45.653 --> 04:48.920
(birds chirping)

04:52.992 --> 04:56.595
(cash register beeps)
(woman) you're gonna have
to muzzle that dog.

04:56.597 --> 04:58.764
(sighs)
(woman)
I know. He's aggressive.

04:58.766 --> 05:01.333
<i>(man) â™ª bring me down</i>

05:01.335 --> 05:02.701
